        void addToInvenotry(Item item)
             throws java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
        Adds a item to the inventory. If the inventory is full and this method is called a 'ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException' will be thrown. It is recommended that checkInventoryFull() and Item.takeItemFromInventory() are used prior to calling this method
